# Zod v4

This project uses **Zod v4** (`^4.4.3`). Many APIs changed between v3 and v4. Always generate v4 patterns. Never generate v3 patterns.

## Import style

```ts
import { z } from 'zod'
```

---

## String format validators ‚Äî top-level functions (v4)

String formats are now top-level functions on `z`. The old method forms are **deprecated** and will be removed.

| ‚úÖ v4 (use this) | ‚ùå v3 (never generate) |
|---|---|
| `z.email()` | `z.string().email()` |
| `z.url()` | `z.string().url()` |
| `z.uuid()` | `z.string().uuid()` |
| `z.cuid()` | `z.string().cuid()` |
| `z.cuid2()` | `z.string().cuid2()` |
| `z.ulid()` | `z.string().ulid()` |
| `z.nanoid()` | `z.string().nanoid()` |
| `z.emoji()` | `z.string().emoji()` |
| `z.base64()` | `z.string().base64()` |
| `z.base64url()` | `z.string().base64url()` |
| `z.ipv4()` | `z.string().ip({ version: 'v4' })` |
| `z.ipv6()` | `z.string().ip({ version: 'v6' })` |
| `z.cidrv4()` | ‚Äî |
| `z.cidrv6()` | ‚Äî |
| `z.iso.date()` | `z.string().date()` |
| `z.iso.time()` | `z.string().time()` |
| `z.iso.datetime()` | `z.string().datetime()` |
| `z.iso.duration()` | `z.string().duration()` |

```ts
// ‚úÖ v4
z.email()
z.uuid()
z.url()
z.iso.datetime()

// ‚ùå v3 ‚Äî never generate these
z.string().email()
z.string().uuid()
z.string().url()
z.string().datetime()
```

