## Object schemas

### Strict / loose objects

```ts
// ‚úÖ v4
z.strictObject({ name: z.string() })   // strips unknown keys + errors
z.looseObject({ name: z.string() })    // passthrough ‚Äî keeps unknown keys

// ‚ùå v3 ‚Äî deprecated
z.object({ name: z.string() }).strict()
z.object({ name: z.string() }).passthrough()
```

Plain `z.object()` still strips unknown keys by default (same as v3).

### Merging / extending objects

```ts
// ‚úÖ preferred in v4 ‚Äî best TypeScript performance
const Extended = z.object({
  ...Base.shape,
  ...Extra.shape,
})

// ‚úÖ also fine
const Extended = Base.extend(Extra.shape)

// ‚ùå deprecated in v4
const Extended = Base.merge(Extra)
```

